&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;h3&gt;The Takeaway&lt;/h3&gt;  &lt;p&gt;When you rectify something you&rsquo;ve done wrong, not only are you displaying your strength, but you're also opening up the space to allow other people to feel safe in making their own mistakes. Making mistakes is inevitable&mdash;that&rsquo;s for certain. And resolving them in a true and honest way is the mark of a real leader. &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Susie Moore is Greatist&rsquo;s life coach columnist and a confidence coach in New York City. Sign up for free weekly wellness tips on her &lt;a href=&quot;http://susie-moore.com&quot;&gt;website&lt;/a&gt; and check back every Tuesday for her latest No Regrets column!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ",
